[http://sourceforge.net/p/ddclient/wiki/Home/ ddclient] is a tool to update dynamic DNS services like DynDNS or no-ip. It runs as daemon and supports many services.

== Installation ==

=== Emerge ===

{{Emerge|net-dns/ddclient}}

=== Fix permissions ===

Use these commands to fix permissions:

{{RootCmd|Secure permissions|output=<pre>
chmod 600 /etc/ddclient/ddclient.conf
chown ddclient:ddclient /etc/ddclient/ddclient.conf
</pre>
}}

== Configuration ==

The configuration is done in the file {{Path|/etc/ddclient/ddclient.conf}}. It must not be world or group readable.

=== no-ip.com ===

Take a look an example configuration for no-ip.com:
{{FileBox|filename=/etc/ddclient/ddclient.conf|1=
use=web, web=checkip.dyndns.com/, web-skip='IP Address'

protocol=dyndns2
server=dynupdate.no-ip.com
login=your_username (typically your email)
password=your_password
your_domain_in_noip.com
}}

